  "notes": "MVE passed all gates (entropy 0.922 > -0.60, no NaN, FPS ~5000). Run A reproduced pre-003 baseline within tolerance (val -39.55 vs historical -51.5, delta 11.95 < 15). Runs B and C executed in parallel. Trade count per episode is much higher than the spec's threshold of 40, but the spec assumed ~23 bars per episode — actual episode length is ~348 bars at bar_size=1000 with these cache files. Cross-evaluation of no-exec-cost models WITH exec cost shows much worse returns (Run B: val -85.22, Run C: val -64.50), indicating the learned policies trade too frequently to survive transaction costs. Run C (199d) has notably lower explained_variance (0.174 at 2M) compared to 20d runs (0.979-0.984), indicating 2M steps is insufficient to learn 199 days of data. Run C entropy stays much higher (0.743 vs 0.490-0.542) confirming the model has not converged. Forced flatten cost still applies even in no-exec-cost condition per the spec's acknowledged confound."
